-- Arabtec Signs Agreement to Develop $681 Million Project in Ras Al Khaimah
-- Zainab Fattah
-- 2010-07-26T05:28:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/arabtec-signs-agreement-to-develop-681-million-project-in-ras-al-khaimah.html

          
          
             Arabtec Holding PJSC , the United
Arab Emirates’ biggest builder, said it signed an accord with
Khoie Properties for the construction of the La Hoya Bay
Development on Ras Al Khaimah’s Marjan Island.  
 The total value of the project is estimated at 2.5 billion
dirhams ($680 million) and it be built in phases over 54 months,
Arabtec said in a statement to the Dubai bourse today.  
 Construction on the project’s first phase, valued at 900
million dirhams, will start immediately after a financing
agreement is signed. The agreement is now in its final stages,
the company said.  
 La Hoya Bay Development , which will be built on 1.5 million
square-feet of land on man-made Marjan Island, is designed to
include homes, hotels, offices, retail space, three marinas and
a yacht club. The project will have 5.5 million square-feet of
built up area, Arabtec said.  
